show_title: GM Farcaster ep242 Wednesday May 7, 2025 with  @poof-eth  @dxrgai Terminal
text:
Why "Pectra"?

Upgrades to the execution layer follow Devcon city names, and those to the consensus layer use star names. "Pectra" is the combination of Prague, the location of Devcon IV, and Electra, a blue-white giant star in the constellation of Taurus.

https://blog.ethereum.org/2025/04/23/pectra-mainnet

text:
Happy Pectra day! üéâ From Octant's side, no protocol-specific changes were needed, but of course we upgraded our nodes.

We haven't seen any drops in the effectiveness of our validators with this upgrade. Initially, network participation dropped to 88% for a couple of hours but has climbed up to 97% since then. This time it was not related to any bugs in any particular client but rather to people forgetting to upgrade their nodes. 

Pectra is smooth sailing thx to the great work of core devs @ethereum ‚ù§Ô∏è

The Forever Library is now immortalized in video by @acsmedia! Thank you to all who contributed their work to our book fair and to all who came and participated. We Alexandrians love you all.

Our online bookshop of limited digital editions is becoming so filled with treasures, I could barely fit the physical representations of them on our book fair table. Original work and classic titles, fiction, nonfiction, and poetry, we‚Äôve got it all.

Special thank yous to @debbie for being our co-host and resident author, to wellread.pt for the curation of books from the Lisbon book shop, to the Singapore Global Network for sponsoring, to /paragraph for their zine display, and to @liface and everyone at Fractal Tech for hosting in their gorgeous space!

Thank you SO MUCH @acsmedia for capturing that day--and welcome to Farcaster!

text:
good morning

i am feeling great with my personal X account unlocked

we shipped our biggest @qrcoindotfun update yet yesterday

it seemed well received and the $QR token is up 70% in the last 24h

the challenge remains that bootstrapping a daily auction is really hard!

but through 2 months, we've survived, and for more of that time than not, we've thrived

so let's see what's in store for month 3

i am optimistic that USDC bidding will expand the range of possible bidders

even though conventional wisdom says no one outside of crypto will touch this stuff

the fact is, if you have a link you like and want to drive some attention to it for a day, you can bid on our auction even if you don't know anything about wallets or crypto, we made it that easy

even if it's not used by normal people, it's important to me to make it at least possible, should they want to

everyone else, i encourage you to open qrcoin.fun (mini app) once daily

never know when you might discover the next great app/coin/person/etc., early
